  "texts": [
    "Another choice model that is compatible with the RUM framework is the paired combinatorial logit (PCL) model.",
    "The PCL model allows for correlations between the utilities of any pair of products to capture situations where the preference of a customer for a particular product offers insights into the customer's attitude towards another product.",
    "Under the PCL model, all products are grouped into nests of size two such that the collection of nests is represented by the set M = {(i, j)|i ≠ j;i, j ∈ N} of ordered pairs.",
    "For each nest (i, j), its dissimilarity parameter ij ∈ [0, 1] characterizes the cor- relation between the utilities of products i and j.",
    "Based on this, the choice process for each arriving customer under the PCL can be modelled in two stages."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}